ection","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BC3E86B2E22745219AAC8A37A98277B1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">In a clean biosafety cabinet, remove serum media from cells (DO NOT TRYPSINIZE!)<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1091511,"guid":"62C06E903C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","previous_id":1091510,"previous_guid":"62BF84303C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B0FA168F98F743F48902E16535C4D9B8","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C04F5E79A777450AA6E22E9F8712D618","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1.5 mL of serum-free cell culture media (DMEM or similar)<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1091512,"guid":"62C158F13C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","previous_id":1091511,"previous_guid":"62C06E903C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E0F45FC32A0A44DCAE3A535D192894FD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3F7D3EECEFA441FDB71852140EDBCC70","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>In a sterile tube dilute total plasmid DNA (\u00b5g) in serum-free DMEM. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">6 well plate:<\/span><span> 200 \u00b5l + 3 \u00b5g of total DNA per well; <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">24 well plate<\/span><span>: 30 \u00b5l + 0.5 \u00b5g of total DNA per well Add PEI (1 \u00b5g\/\u00b5L) to the diluted DNA. Mix immediately by vortexing or pipetting. The volume of PEI used is based on a 3:1 ratio of PEI (\u00b5g):total DNA (\u00b5g). This ratio can be optimized to maximize transfection efficiency. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">    a.\t6-well plate: 9 \u00b5l of PEI(1 \u00b5g\/\u00b5l) = 9 \u00b5g PEI to 3 \u00b5g DNA <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">    b.\tYou will need 200 \u00b5L serum-free DMEM + 3 \u00b5gDNA+9 \u00b5g PEI for each well of a 6-well plate you plan to transfect.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">    c.\t24 well plate: 1.5 \u00b5l of PEI(1 \u00b5g\/\u00b5l) = 1.5 \u00b5g PEI to 0.5 \u00b5g DNA <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">    d.\tYou will need 30 \u00b5l serum-free DMEM + 0.5 \u00b5g DNA + 1.5 \u00b5g PEI for each well of a 24-well plate.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1091513,"guid":"62C243503C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","previous_id":1091512,"previous_guid":"62C158F13C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A9252AF7225C4B9583FB490DF65B5713","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BEB51FEDCA674A489101CB3FECF9584F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For the negative control, add 9 \u00b5g PEI to 200 \u00b5L serum-free media - no plasmid DNA.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1091514,"guid":"62C32DB13C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","previous_id":1091513,"previous_guid":"62C243503C0A11EBAE5AFB12EA12FE63","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0C9722C9C6194A9EACE54D2CF23D7405","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"478